Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.18,0:00:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,SATAN.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.85,0:00:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.21,0:00:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Devil!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.40,0:00:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But two letters still remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.53,0:00:15.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too early to determine it's Satan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.92,0:00:17.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the two lines remaining are...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.44,0:00:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I am a long-nosed wizard in a castle," and...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.11,0:00:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Pierce the white back using two swords," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.66,0:00:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're creeping me out before even\Nwe've started looking for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.20,0:00:31.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as "I'm a long-nosed wizard in a castle," I know where that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.29,0:00:35.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one with a long nose is the "elephant".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.63,0:00:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then there's "castle".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.25,0:00:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In London, there's an area called "Elephant & Castle".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.80,0:00:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check that out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.26,0:00:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what part of that area should we go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.43,0:00:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try the station for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.01,0:00:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.93,0:00:51.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll go check out the Elephant & Castle Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.23,0:00:55.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the deciding moment that determines your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.17,0:00:57.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cannot lie to yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.64,0:01:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll will can be seen hidden deep in the code...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.65,0:01:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the culprit's target?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.36,0:01:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.95,0:01:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.91,0:01:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.76,0:02:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What awaited us in London was a creepy, ciphered note.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.18,0:02:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a manifesto for the next crime of\NHades Sabara, a heinous criminal on the run.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.94,0:03:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each line in the cipher represented\Na distinctive building in London...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.78,0:03:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And each location held a hidden hint that\Nreferred to the titles of Holmes stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.87,0:03:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each hint was an alphabet letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.79,0:03:20.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We made progress in deciphering it, and\Nobtained five such letters from the alphabet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.92,0:03:22.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only two remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.17,0:03:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just you wait, Hades.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.92,0:03:30.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall definitely solve this code and put a stop to your crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.00,0:03:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.31,0:03:45.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've arrived at the station and searched for almost an hour, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.86,0:03:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't found a thing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.49,0:03:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.11,0:03:52.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this really the right place?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.16,0:03:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think it's the right place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.12,0:04:00.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it could also mean a shopping mall in the same area.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.00,0:04:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.59,0:04:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hasn't that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.55,0:04:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Been walking back and forth the entire time we've been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.55,0:04:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.26,0:04:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.22,0:04:15.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see a man carrying an attach√© case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.76,0:04:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it has "Identity" written on it in big letters!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.73,0:04:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.27,0:04:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Case of Identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.52,0:04:27.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the title of a Holmes story, known as "The\NCase of the Disappearing Bridegroom" in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.28,0:04:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ask that man about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.95,0:04:38.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like he was paid by somebody to loiter around\Nthis station in the same manner for the entire day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.37,0:04:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said that both the empty case and the clothes\Nhe's wearing were given to him by that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.08,0:04:45.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The clothes too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.25,0:04:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"My first glance is always at a woman's sleeve.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.55,0:04:54.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"In a man it is perhaps better first to take the knee of the trouser."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.05,0:04:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The knees of his trousers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.47,0:04:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try looking at that man's knees!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.23,0:05:01.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His knees?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.52,0:05:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there's nothing written there...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:06.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then try rolling it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.07,0:05:08.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.52,0:05:10.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, what're you doing here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.07,0:05:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.28,0:05:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the inside of his pants near the knee is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.66,0:05:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The letter U!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.95,0:05:18.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Putting it all together...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.41,0:05:23.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T, N, A, A, S, U.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The remaining cipher is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.17,0:05:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last line, "It tells me to finish everything by\Npiercing the white back with two swords," but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.17,0:05:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm stuck at the "white back" and "two swords" parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.89,0:05:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There aren't any buildings or places with those shapes or names...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.60,0:05:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, this is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.56,0:05:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the mark for a porcelain maker!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.23,0:05:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By "pierce the white back with two swords" he means...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two-sword trademark on the back of this\Nporcelain tableware famous for its white color!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.41,0:06:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, our next stop is a store for that porcelain maker in London?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.04,0:06:06.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's that store, I went there a lot with my mum!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.96,0:06:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since my mum's favorite is that brand of porcelain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.46,0:06:13.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's only one store in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.01,0:06:16.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange decorations?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.34,0:06:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.22,0:06:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked the store staff...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.76,0:06:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they said they've been troubled by someone\Nhanging strange decorations on their sign each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.85,0:06:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of decoration was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.14,0:06:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are threads of various colors with a bell attached at the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.40,0:06:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a letter is written on each bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.90,0:06:36.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where the threads are tied together, there are some\Nwords that look like a title written there, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.32,0:06:39.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's stained and I can't quite make it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.95,0:06:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That title is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.16,0:06:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Study in Scarlet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:48.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's where Conan Doyle first conceived\NSherlock Holmes into this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.13,0:06:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His debut case, and we call it "Hiiro no Kenkyuu"!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.21,0:06:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Find a scarlet thread from that bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.30,0:06:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is, the thread that's a vivid red color.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.09,0:07:01.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The line Holmes says in that story goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.64,0:07:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"There's the scarlet thread of murder running\Nthrough the colorless skein of life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.27,0:07:15.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And our duty is to unravel it, and\Nisolate it, and expose every inch of it."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.53,0:07:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.57,0:07:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The red thread!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.99,0:07:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One the bell attached to that thread, the letter R is written!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.70,0:07:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If R is the last letter, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.50,0:07:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The keywords are T, N, A, A, S, U, and R‚Äîthose seven letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.43,0:07:37.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If five of those makes SATAN...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.34,0:07:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do the remaining U and R mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.76,0:07:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.85,0:07:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, looks like we can leave it as just one A.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.68,0:07:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The letters are arranged...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:56.53,Signs,,0,0,0,,SATURN...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.90,0:07:57.78,Signs,,0,0,0,,The "Soil Planet"!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.53,0:07:59.78,Signs,,0,0,0,,So the culprit probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.40,0:08:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Intends to commit something on Saturday, or "Soil Day"!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.28,0:08:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soil Day...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.91,0:08:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, that's tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.50,0:08:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, wait, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.21,0:08:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although we can associate "Soil Planet"\Nwith "Soil Day" in Japanese...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.46,0:08:18.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,English speakers don't call the sixth planet\Nin the solar system "Soil Planet", do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.80,0:08:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.76,0:08:24.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The etymology for Saturday comes from the\Nagricultural god of Roman mythology, Saturnus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.51,0:08:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saturnus's Day became Saturday...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.27,0:08:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Saturnus is pronounced Saturn in English!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.79,0:08:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.06,0:08:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's going to happen on Saturday, and where?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.57,0:08:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apollo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.15,0:08:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounds Apollo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.28,0:08:42.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mum!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.57,0:08:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know I was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.41,0:08:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The solution of the code brought me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.66,0:08:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last sentence might hint this boutique...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.91,0:08:53.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? I told you so, Ares...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.79,0:08:55.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.21,0:08:57.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You deserve to be a Sherlockian...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.34,0:09:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, we are going back to the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow we are going to watch Minerva's game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.85,0:09:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.43,0:09:11.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave the code to us and go with your mama, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.68,0:09:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.31,0:09:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, your mother said they're going to go and cheer, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.27,0:09:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, your mother's eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.73,0:09:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though she can't see, she can tell by the sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.25,0:09:27.13,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Juno Glass (22)\NMinerva's Mother
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.61,0:09:25.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's why Mum always goes to the finals at the very least.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.93,0:09:31.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Since Mum didn't go to cheer for her at the French\NOpen tennis finals last year, and my sister lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.50,0:09:31.21,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ares Ashley (30)\NMinerva's Former Coach
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.20,0:09:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apollo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.79,0:09:34.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be an angel and jump in the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.25,0:09:38.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I broke all of the codes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't find out what and where it will happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.09,0:09:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course you can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.47,0:09:49.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you didn't break them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.52,0:09:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I gave you a chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.73,0:09:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's your fault that you can't stop my final revenge...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.19,0:10:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you couldn't read my revelations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.90,0:10:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Curse your incompetence...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.12,0:10:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holmes's apprentice is on your side, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.70,0:10:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll make it clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.83,0:10:19.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holmes's apprentice?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.88,0:10:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.34,0:10:34.33,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Geez, what a carefree person...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.70,0:10:40.53,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's Saturday, and even though a mass murder\Ncould happen somewhere in London today...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.15,0:10:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's still out there walking her dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.03,0:10:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've informed Scotland Yard about how the\Ncipher becomes "Saturday" when solved, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.16,0:10:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.20,0:10:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told them how each of the seven lines in\Nthe cipher indicated a building or place...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.04,0:11:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was one letter of the keyword hidden at each place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And together they formed SATURN, meaning Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.34,0:11:08.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the culprit was probably\Nintending to do something on Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.63,0:11:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I explained everything, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.64,0:11:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They came back with, "Which Saturday is it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.68,0:11:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And hung up on me after saying, "If we don't know when,\Nwhere, or what's going to happen, we can't do anything."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.52,0:11:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that detective brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.36,0:11:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.44,0:11:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi said he's got another investigation\Nto work on, so he'll leave the rest to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.07,0:11:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave the rest to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.74,0:11:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've solved the cipher which was the only clue, and figured\Nout that something's going to happen on Saturday, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.37,0:11:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What else is there to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.21,0:11:41.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.04,0:11:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's still something left unsolved in the cipher.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.34,0:11:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you only need one A to spell out the keyword SATURN...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.97,0:11:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't there be another reason why Big Ben,\Nwhere that A was found, appears twice in the cipher?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.35,0:11:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.39,0:11:59.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you get over your cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.10,0:12:00.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.94,0:12:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm still coughing a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.23,0:12:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell is with this Hades Sabara guy anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.53,0:12:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he give out a ciphered manifesto of his crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.41,0:12:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's probably a self-aggrandizing man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.24,0:12:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Previously, he sent advance warning riddles\Nfor the hospital bombings as well, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.08,0:12:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he blew up the hospital, he deliberately sent the\Npolice a videotape he took of the destruction...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.96,0:12:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which was enclosed along with a letter explaining the riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.05,0:12:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.68,0:12:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was saying, "Catch me if you can," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.68,0:12:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, we need to hurry and figure out\Nthe cipher's true meaning to tell the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.94,0:12:46.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to proceed the matter with caution, though
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.44,0:12:51.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the case of the second hospital, they\Nhad somehow solved the riddle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.61,0:12:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But right after the bomb disposal team went in, he set the bomb off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.41,0:12:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.66,0:13:00.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he'll commit it whether the cipher is solved or not!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.91,0:13:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It also seems he sent a video of that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.88,0:13:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It contained his laughing voice saying,\N"You're too late!" recorded on the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.05,0:13:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So in order to stop his crime, it looks like we'd have to solve\Nthe cipher completely and sneak over to that place...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.51,0:13:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And secretly creep up to that man and capture him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:23.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, the City Hall and the Gherkin...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.48,0:13:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were on the opposite sides of the River Thames.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.15,0:13:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were at places shown in the\Ncipher, did you see anyone suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.86,0:13:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.16,0:13:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.58,0:13:39.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw a woman wearing sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.75,0:13:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.04,0:13:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.33,0:13:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's an explosives expert who used to work with Hades.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.84,0:13:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if she looked like that or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.38,0:13:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.55,0:13:54.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's balloons!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.80,0:13:56.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bastard Hades...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.14,0:13:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will probably attach bombs to balloons and set them loose, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.26,0:14:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, starting with Big Ben at the beginning of the code...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.35,0:14:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We connect it to the Elephant & Castle\NStation from the second line...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.48,0:14:09.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And go to the City Hall from the third line.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.69,0:14:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, crossing the River Thames, we arrive\Nat the Gherkin from the fourth line.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.03,0:14:18.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Going through St. Bride's Church from the fifth line...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.99,0:14:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And returning to Big Ben for the sixth line.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.87,0:14:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, with the last line...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.08,0:14:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We head over to the porcelain store on Walton Street...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.54,0:14:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.21,0:14:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks just like a balloon, doesn't it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.76,0:14:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason Big Ben appeared twice is because we need to\Nconnect the locations in the order shown in the code!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.14,0:14:47.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that shape...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.73,0:14:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather than a balloon...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.06,0:14:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.27,0:14:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.57,0:14:57.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're looking for this man, have you seen him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.40,0:14:58.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.49,0:15:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seemed to have entered the toilet you came out of...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.58,0:15:04.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.50,0:15:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's known to be the mass murderer terrifying the people in London...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.17,0:15:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he seems to have changed his appearance to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.17,0:15:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I haven't seen him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.92,0:15:19.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to have disturbed you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.30,0:15:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, he won't be around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.85,0:15:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I guess so...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.39,0:15:27.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incompetent fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.52,0:15:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, there's no one who can even come close to my level.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.74,0:15:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a little lonely without any resistance from them...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.70,0:15:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is my final offering of revenge for my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.12,0:15:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not too bad for everything to end peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.70,0:15:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.79,0:15:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For my mother's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.83,0:15:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall silence this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.96,0:15:53.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where the cheers echo...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.72,0:15:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this Wimbledon Centre Court!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.18,0:16:04.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I, as Hades Sabara!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.14,0:16:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.93,0:16:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A tennis racquet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.77,0:16:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not a balloon?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.02,0:16:13.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.36,0:16:17.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a little warped, but it does seem to me like a racquet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.61,0:16:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.69,0:16:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we're talking about tennis in London...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.11,0:16:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wimbledon!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.74,0:16:25.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minerva{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will begin her final match at 2:00 PM today!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.12,0:16:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't Wimbledon wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.00,0:16:38.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought if he had told all the children he gave that cipher to, "A\Nperson will die right before your eyes," it'd be wrong, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.09,0:16:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the police haven't issued a warning about a mass murder yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.18,0:16:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably only told those words to Apollo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.60,0:16:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the reason he also passed the cipher to other kids\Nwas to confuse the investigation with false leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.77,0:16:56.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, someone dying before Apollo's eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.44,0:17:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Means that the culprit's target is likely in\Nthe Wimbledon Ladies' Singles final!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.36,0:17:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why Wimbledon?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.87,0:17:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it has something to do with tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.03,0:17:11.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the culprit passed the cipher to\NApollo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} inside of Wimbledon too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.96,0:17:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps that "something" was the bookie?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.08,0:17:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know his mother died of heart disease...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.59,0:17:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last July.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.17,0:17:25.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it seems that, a month before, Hades placed\Na losing bet with a bookie on some sort of game.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.68,0:17:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, Minerva{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} lost at the French Open last year...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.10,0:17:32.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that final match was in June, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.69,0:17:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, she had won all her matches up until the\Nfinal, which she had to drop out of due to injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.19,0:17:43.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if Hades had to come up with the rest of the\Ncost needed for his mother's operation...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.45,0:17:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And had placed all his money on her sure\Nwin at the French Open tennis...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.79,0:17:53.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd lost the bet and all of his money, causing\Nher mother to forgo her operation and died!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.25,0:17:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be that the culprit's target is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.75,0:17:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Grass Court Queen...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.67,0:18:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minerva Glass!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.60,0:18:15.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she's all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:16.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.02,0:18:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With Mum here, she'll win for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.56,0:18:20.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, is it all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.86,0:18:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're always in the general admission seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.99,0:18:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.11,0:18:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dislike sitting in the family box.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.03,0:18:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The TV cameras will zoom in on me since\NI don't appear to be watching the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.20,0:18:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if Minerva sees my footage in the middle\Nof her match, she may get distracted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.71,0:18:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even so, that child...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.96,0:18:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She always seems to find me when the match is about to be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.05,0:18:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, it's such a shame...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.84,0:18:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think this is the last time we'll be watching a match with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.39,0:18:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd even thought that you would do me\Nthe honour of becoming my son-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.85,0:18:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I cannot take your daughter when I've\Nalready taken your husband from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.77,0:19:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is it true that you're going to be someone else's coach?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.40,0:19:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.28,0:19:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it'll be awkward for me to see you all again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.16,0:19:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.66,0:19:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your sister is doing well enough even without me, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.75,0:19:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.33,0:19:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already after 2:00, y'know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.46,0:19:20.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The match is already starting!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.21,0:19:24.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what are we going to do after we get to Wimbledon?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.13,0:19:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't even have tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.05,0:19:29.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For that, where there's a will, there's a way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.77,0:19:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A will...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.66,0:19:33.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.64,0:19:35.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you reached Apollo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.27,0:19:36.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.39,0:19:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably turned his phone off while watching the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.69,0:19:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.44,0:19:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apollo!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.48,0:19:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.03,0:19:46.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You never called me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.12,0:19:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.49,0:19:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.78,0:19:53.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't take the call in the seats, so I came out to the passageway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.49,0:19:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, since you called me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.33,0:20:00.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does it mean the culprit who gave me that code has been captured?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.21,0:20:02.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not yet, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.13,0:20:05.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then don't call me now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.21,0:20:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm watching my sister's game!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.47,0:20:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.47,0:20:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has anything strange happened at the court?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.59,0:20:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like if anyone has spoken to you, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.72,0:20:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, some of my sister's fans said "good luck" to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.52,0:20:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since they recognised me, Mum, and Ares...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.60,0:20:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They gave us a huge stuffed animal and said it's for my sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.90,0:20:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And how's your sister doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.07,0:20:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How she's doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.99,0:20:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's just the usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.07,0:20:35.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her match just started, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.08,0:20:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why are you asking me this stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.37,0:20:41.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, something's going to happen here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.00,0:20:42.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.46,0:20:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's nothing like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.13,0:20:49.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just that we wanted to watch your sister's game.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.38,0:20:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any extra tickets?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.93,0:20:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Extra?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.47,0:20:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He can't possibly have some...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.06,0:20:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Extra tickets, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.06,0:21:01.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we're here in front of the gates...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.44,0:21:06.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though we know there's a heinous\Ncriminal somewhere inside that court...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.27,0:21:08.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, I've no other choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.65,0:21:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.69,0:21:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Sleeping Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.78,0:21:17.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you here for the game?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.87,0:21:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Diana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.08,0:21:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot our tickets!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.46,0:21:23.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you help me with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.79,0:21:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about this idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.47,0:21:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.26,0:21:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As long as we have admission tickets,\Neven if we can't get into Centre Court...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.97,0:21:41.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can still watch the final on this huge screen here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.77,0:21:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is the famous Murray Mound...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.39,0:21:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we sure were lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.69,0:21:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Diana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has influence within the Steering Committee\Nhere, and immediately arranged for admission tickets for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.90,0:21:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, we weren't able to push our luck as\Nto obtain tickets for Centre Court though...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.66,0:22:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who the hell is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.41,0:22:03.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.00,0:22:06.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, how's the match going?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.79,0:22:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Minerva{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} isn't in her top condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.63,0:22:13.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of her serves are catching the net...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.13,0:22:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she's losing with a score of 3-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.72,0:22:19.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.64,0:22:20.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First service!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.06,0:22:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please... somebody...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.44,0:22:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anybody, help...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.44,0:22:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Help me...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.74,0:22:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holmes...!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.53,0:24:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister's being targeted by the culprit!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.03,0:24:04.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a little longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.33,0:24:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a little longer, Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.79,0:24:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way they'd exist in this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.29,0:24:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone like Sherlock Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.75,0:24:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll help you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.71,0:24:16.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Holmes's apprentice!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.67,0:24:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holmes's...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.97,0:24:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apprentice?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.72,0:24:42.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.80,0:24:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stuffed Bear
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.79,0:24:49.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look Forward to the Next Episode
